.TH CALCCU 1 "June 2026" "calccu 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
calccu \- live terminal calculator with variables, functions, units, and equation solving
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B calccu
.br
.B calccu
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ expression ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B calccu
is an interactive terminal calculator. It shows a bounded live preview while
input is edited, evaluates expressions with Enter, stores the latest result in
.BR ans ,
and keeps a short visible session history above the prompt.
.PP
Automatic answers are displayed as values. Named assignments and equation
solutions keep their names.
.PP
When an expression is passed on the command line,
.B calccu
evaluates it and exits. When standard input is not a terminal,
.B calccu
evaluates each non-empty input line and exits.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help text and exit.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.BI "--precision " n
Set displayed significant digits for this run. The value must be between 1 and
15.
.TP
.B --plain
Print display-form output. Automatic answers are values; named assignments and
equation solutions are printed unchanged.
.TP
.B --json
Print one JSON object per evaluated expression. This applies to command-line
expressions and standard input batches.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start interactive mode:
.EX
calccu
.EE
.TP
Evaluate one expression:
.EX
calccu "2 + 2"
.EE
Set precision for one run:
.EX
calccu --precision 6 "1 / 3"
.EE
.TP
Print JSON:
.EX
calccu --json "5km -> m"
.EE
.TP
Convert units:
.EX
calccu "5km to m"
calccu "5km -> m"
calccu "2 meters to cm"
calccu "32F -> C"
.EE
.TP
Solve equations:
.EX
calccu "2x = 3"
calccu "x^2 - 4 = 0"
.EE
.TP
Use built-in math functions:
.EX
calccu "gcd(12, 18)"
calccu "lcm(4, 6)"
calccu "fact(5)"
.EE
.TP
Read expressions from standard input:
.EX
printf "2 + 2\\n32F to C\\n" | calccu
.EE
