.SH MATH
.B calccu
supports the operators
.BR + ,
.BR - ,
.BR * ,
.BR / ,
and
.BR ^ ,
parentheses, implicit multiplication such as
.BR 2x ,
variables, user-defined functions, unit conversion with
.BR to ,
the constants
.B pi
and
.BR e ,
and the latest result variable
.BR ans .
.PP
Basic finite decimal and integer arithmetic is kept exact, avoiding common
floating-point artifacts such as
.BR "0.1 + 0.2" .
.B gcd ,
.B lcm ,
and
.B fact
also use exact integer arithmetic.
Built-in transcendental functions and unit conversion factors use JavaScript
numbers where approximation is expected.
.PP
Built-in functions include
.BR abs ,
.BR acos ,
.BR asin ,
.BR atan ,
.BR cbrt ,
.BR ceil ,
.BR cos ,
.BR exp ,
.BR fact ,
.BR factorial ,
.BR floor ,
.BR gcd ,
.BR hypot ,
.BR lcm ,
.BR ln ,
.BR log ,
.BR log2 ,
.BR max ,
.BR min ,
.BR round ,
.BR sign ,
.BR sin ,
.BR sqrt ,
.BR tan ,
and
.BR trunc .
.PP
Common aliases and plural names are accepted for many units, such as
.BR meter ,
.BR metres ,
.BR feet ,
.BR hours ,
and
.BR bytes .
Unknown unit-like names include suggestions when there is a close match.
.PP
Equation solving supports exact single-variable linear equations and quadratic
equations up to degree two.
.SH UNITS
Supported unit categories are temperature, length, weight, area, volume,
energy, speed, time, and data.
.PP
Canonical output uses short unit symbols such as
.BR m ,
.BR ft ,
.BR h ,
and
.BR B .
.PP
Use the
.B units
interactive command to list all supported unit symbols.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CALCCU_HISTORY
Path to the interactive command history file. Overrides the XDG default.
.TP
.B XDG_STATE_HOME
Base directory for the default interactive command history file. Defaults to
.BR ~/.local/state .
.SH FILES
.TP
.B $XDG_STATE_HOME/calccu/history
Default interactive command history file.
.TP
.B ~/.local/state/calccu/history
Default interactive command history file when
.B XDG_STATE_HOME
is unset.
